Hugging Face Transformers vs Ollama - 
Because I'm using google collab for this project I'll probably use hugging face transformers.
Ollama is great for running models on your own laptop, but in Colab it causes headaches because it expects to manage its own server process.

ChromaDB over Qdrant - 
ChromaDB is simpler to set up in Colab with no external server needed
Qdrant in its full form expects a running Docker container or a cloud instance, which would require workarounds
Qdrant does have an in-memory Python client mode but then you lose the persistence advantage anyway* 
(Qdrant može da radi brzo u Pythonu bez instalacije pravog servera, ali ako ga koristiš samo u memoriji (in-memory), on se ponaša kao obična promenljiva. Ako ti se Colab ugasi, 
moraš ponovo da radiš ceo document ingestion i ponovo generišeš sve embeddinge)
ChromaDB saves directly to Colab's local disk (or Google Drive) with almost no configuration
